annotation.TEXT: Vanilla Secret Yu
Bonus game average so far: 1 / 1 = 1 1-up each.
Oh, man. We've got maces now. Be careful of them while solving this puzzle.
No Yoshi because I dumped him into the pit in Switch Thwomp's Fortress for the third time.
It doesn't look possible to get all of the coins here, but I think the coins are meant as hints to the Podoboos' heights.
:) demo count: 2
I Can't Go Back Anymore
Ah, yes. If I bounce off one of these red parakoopas and glide to the right, I should be able to stomp the shell-less green duder up ahead and reach the goal that way.

Alright, there's one more way to reach the goal, and it's similar to the previous one. If I press A at the exact right time as I walk off the edge of a ledge while at running speed, I can do a spin jump flight. I'll use the turbo A button to help me with this one.
Goal tape average so far: 191 / 8 = 23.875 stars each.
Now it gets really tricky. In some cases, you may have to loop around after hitting an ON/OFF block just to hit that same block again, because of the ! blocks' positions.
Note: There was a late vote for the 1st one alphabetically, which I believe would be :), so that means that :) actually got 10 votes, which wouldn't have changed the outcome.
May as well get what little I can in the way of bonus stars...
Goal tape average so far: 86 / 5 = 17.2 stars each.

Alright, back here again. Now, apparently, even though jumping doesn't seem to be of any use here, if you build up running speed while caped, it'll still allow you to enter cape-flying mode if you leave the ground shortly after attempting to jump, like this!
Goal tape average so far: 79 / 4 = 19.75 stars each.
More ON/OFF shenanigans with parakoopas and maces.
Yeah, I kind of screwed that up...
...Uh, oh. I think I screwed up. Well, now I have no choice but to fly out of bounds and lose a :) life, but I still have 4 left.
Oh, man. So this is where that saw noise was coming from. The path to take involves a lot of ups and downs, and you have to do a lot of dodging along the way.
Alright, there's the goal! Just don't stupidly crash into the parakoopa or press a direction besides right and the level is done!

Now, clearing :) doesn't reveal any new paths, regardless of whether or not you've played any other levels and revealed other paths. And no, the game still won't let me go north to the castle from :), even though it looks like I should be able to.

Bingo!
Also, one of them shoots Missile Bills, which turn around once. At least they're not those evil homing bullets that I've seen in some other hacks!
FINISH!!! (And since I didn't run out of :) lives, Mario himself never died, so his demo count will remain at zero.)
:P :P :P
Hmm... I'm not going to be able to collect the upper pair of coins here.

Okay, I think I've had enough of hitting this goal point. Thanks go to all of you who suggested these different methods! Now, which level will I play next? Well, that's for the voting results to decide...
Aha. If I didn't hit that rightmost ON/OFF block twice in a row to begin with, I would've been blocked from reaching the goal by an ! block.
BARF! Moved a bit too early there.

Just straight up parakoopa dodging here.
:P

This one's easy. Zwee!
Yeah, yeah. Save prompt because of the debug thing. Whatever. Okay, now back to NOJUNP NOLIFE.
The goal is to guide the :) face to the star block to clear the current screen and advance to the next screen.
Okay, there's one cape, but I may as well get another one as a reserve backup, since I can quickly do so right here.

Of course, this is frame-perfect, and the turbo A button only presses A every other frame, so I think I've only got a 50-50 chance of getting this to work, but if it fails, I can Start+Select out and try again.

Argh! I tried to duck under that unfriendly upside-down saw's hitbox, but it didn't work. Good thing I thought to get that backup cape, but I'd better not screw up again, or I'll have to make more trips to Switch Thwomp's Fortress.
Alright! ...Uh, oh. More of that orange soda with Podoboos coming out of it...
Well, there are just a few levels left. Place your vote for which one you want me to play next time! To be continued... :P
Now, if I lose all of my :) lives, I assume I'd reenter the level either on this screen or the screen with the midpoint.
However, that's not the only way to reach that goal. Let's try a different method...
However, it won't count as a player death unless the :) loses all of its lives. The :) starts with 5 lives, as you can see in the lower-left corner.
Oh, and if you lose a :) on a screen with ON/OFF blocks, the game will set them to ON when your next :) appears, so that the puzzle still works properly.
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 2 - Stickerbrush Symphony
And then, obviously, just fly to the goal. I want to get a decent number of bonus stars this time.
I'm kind of murdering my goal tape average, though... Oh, well. Now, let's go to ludicrous speed for a moment...
Go left to the ON/OFF block first. This way, the ! block will be solid when you go for the goal.
Let's try that again, with less mace in the smiley face this time.
I'll speed up some of this footage here...
This time, the path that I need to take will allow me to collect all of the coins, which appear to once again be hinting at how high the Podoboos go.
Bah! :(
Gotta go down for the ON/OFF switch first to get the ! block outta the way.
Here's some more orange soda.
Bye, Yoshi! I'm not even gonna try to keep you alive this time.
Goal tape average so far: 151 / 7 = 21.571 stars each.
Mmm... Looks delicious... Also, it's nice that Cirno seems to be enjoying autumn.
And thus ends one of the coolest SMW hack levels ever!
And now, normal speed bonus game!

Okay, now with this note block here, if I press A with the right timing as I bounce off of it, I can actually enter "spin jump" mode (this also works even when my jumping isn't restricted, so it can even be done in the original SMW). Then, I can bounce off of the saws to the left and reach the goal that way!
:) demo count: 4
Alright, so let's see here... What's one of the methods that I can try using to reach that early goal?
Very good.
Watch out. There are enemies on a lot of the screens. If the :) hits any of them, or it hits the edge of the screen, then the :) loses a life and has to start the screen over.
Uh, oh. The goal is blocked. But, by going left and then right again to rehit this ON/OFF block, the path to the goal opens up!

Hello, and welcome back to :P :P :P, or :P:P:P for short! Now, before I get to the voting results, I've been informed of many ways to reach the early goal in NOJUNP NOLIFE, which I'll want to show off. And, to do that, I'll need a cape, which I can easily get in Switch Thwomp's Fortress. (Or I could use the debug thing, but I'm not gonna do that.)
40 is way better than what I got the last few times!
No Yoshis because they cannot grasp the true form of Giygas' attack!
Sacrificial horse count: 3
:P
:P
For instance, now ON/OFF blocks are added to the mix. Whenever the :) bumps into an ON/OFF block, it toggles the state of the switches, which in turn toggles the state of the ! blocks here.
Alright, so in this level, you control the :) face there. You can move it with any of the four directional keys, but once it starts moving, it will not stop until it hits something.
Excellent!
Also, the "word" Yu in Vanilla Secret Yu was probably due to the hacker changing the number graphics into Japanese character(s).
Oh, man. I'm on my last :) life here. If I screw up one more time, it's back to midpoint for me!

Now, if the :) does run out of lives, Mario himself will die, and you'll be sent back to the overworld, meaning you'll have to start these puzzles all over (or restart from midpoint if you got that far).
Yeah, there's where I needed to hit an ON/OFF block twice in a row. Otherwise, the goal would've been blocked off on approach to it later.
So far, so good, but these puzzles will get way trickier.
So, :) it is, and this level is way different than the other levels here!
Whoa, man. This is tricky.
Oh, man. So many ON/OFF blocks. I think I have to hit one of the rightmost ones twice in a row at some point.
Okay, so instead of bouncing off that green duder there, I'll just keep going to the right, into saw country.
Gotta avoid the Thwimp, mace, and both parakoopas here. This looks tricky.
Hey, hey! Alright! I got it on the first try! Well, there you go!
Oh, man. Bullet Bills. However, this screen isn't too difficult. And take note that bullet cannons in the column that the :) is touching will not fire.
